; Regression test for issue #1604: Every N days problem in budgeting (BZ#532)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1604
;
; Bug: 'every N weeks from [date]' does not honor the start date for subsequent
; occurrences. Instead it aligns to week boundaries, causing the second budget
; entry to appear too early.
;
; 'every 14 days from 2010/03/01' correctly produces: Mar 1, Mar 15, Mar 29
; 'every 2 weeks from 2010/03/01' incorrectly produces: Mar 1, Mar 7, Mar 21
; (Mar 1 is a Monday, so Mar 7 is the next Sunday/week boundary - only 6 days
; later instead of 14 days later as expected)
;
; Current behavior (broken): Mar 7 appears as a second budget date - only 6
; days after Mar 1, instead of the expected Mar 15 (14 days later).

~ every 2 weeks from 2010/03/01
    Expenses:Bills        $100.00
    Assets:Checking

test reg --budget --now=2010/04/01
10-Mar-01 Budget transaction    Expenses:Bills             $-100.00     $-100.00
10-Mar-01 Budget transaction    Assets:Checking             $100.00            0
10-Mar-07 Budget transaction    Expenses:Bills             $-100.00     $-100.00
10-Mar-07 Budget transaction    Assets:Checking             $100.00            0
10-Mar-21 Budget transaction    Expenses:Bills             $-100.00     $-100.00
10-Mar-21 Budget transaction    Assets:Checking             $100.00            0
end test
